Character Kits (Prestige Class or Alternate Class Feature)
OK	- Arena Mage --> ACF (Familiar)
		- cast spell covertly (85% chance of success)
		- psionic mimicry
OK	- Cerulean --> PC (10-level) min-level 3rd
OK		- must be chaotic
		- must roll to see how many spells per day
OK		- impossible to disguise
		- 5%/level/day of calling Tyr-storm in 15km radius
	- Chasseur --> PC (5-level) min-level 8th
		- gather information, intimidation, survival
		- Track
		- reputation: +2 diplomacy
		- cry witch: accuse of wizardry
	- Earth Defender --> PC (5-level) min-level 5th
		- must be preserver
		- must be nonlawful
		- Hide in plain sight (as ranger)
		- +1/level in Knowledge (nature)
		- +1 in all saves when in chosen ward
		- must help another defender
	- Exterminator --> PC (5-level) min-level 5th
		- must be defiler
		- can revert plant growth and {ward}
		- can create poison of only one type
		- get the most of the terrain
		- refuse to leave area until plant life is exterminated
		- defiler radius x 1.5
OK	- Free Wizard --> No changes
OK	- Illusionist --> No changes
OK	- Mercenary --> No changes
OK	- Necromancer --> ACF (5th level bonus feat)
		- Rebuke undead
	- Restorationist --> PC (10-level) min-level 5th
		- must be preserver
		- must be nonevil
		- Path Dexter
		- domain spell --> Plant/Animal
		- speak with plants (4th-level) 1/day
		- doubled casting time
	- Shadow Wizard --> PC (10-level) min-level 5th
		- must be neutral
		- must roll to see how many spells per day
		- becomes more shadow at each level
		- 5th: chill touch 1/day
		- 7th: speak with shadow
		- 9th: immune to cold
		- absence of shadow (total darkness): fort check or 1d4 damage
